summarizing data

things to look for:
  - missing values
  - outliers / strange data
  - wrong units
  - mislabeled columns 
  - etc

useful functions:
  dim()
  names()
  quantile()
  summary()
  class()
  unique() -- used with qualitative and discrete variables 
  table() -- used with qualitative and discrete variables
    table(A, B) -- shows the relationship between A and B as a table. (rows drawn from A)


any(<boolean expression>) -- check for NA, or outliers
all(<boolean expression>)

complex boolean expressions:
  & -- AND
  | -- OR

ex: data[ A > 10 & B < 20, cols]

rowSums, rowMeans, and their column counterparts